documentation.text:
@dev Registers a name for a given owner.  This registers the name,
 transfers it, and then sets operator permissions for the delegation
 contract with the owner's prepared signature.  With this method, we
 can enable gas-free name registration with this contract's support
 for meta transactions.  Returns the new token's ID.
 The WCHI for the name registration is paid for by _msgSender.

documentation.text:
@dev Takes over a name:  This transfers the name to be owned by
 the delegation contract (which is irreversible and corresponds to
 a provable "lock" of the name).  This can only be done by the owner
 of the name.  The previous owner will be granted top-level permissions,
 based on which they can then selectively restrict their access if desired.

devdoc.details: The main delegation contract.  It uses the permissions tree system implemented in the super contracts, and links it to the actual XayaAccounts contract for sending moves.  It also enables ERC2771 meta transactions.

constructor.details: Constructs the contract, fixing the XayaAccounts as well as forwarder contracts.

expireTree(uint256,address,string[]).details: Removes all expired permissions in the given subtree.  This may have an indirect effect on fallback permissions, but otherwise does not alter permissions (since it only removes ones that are expired anyway at the current time).  Everyone is allowed to call this if they are willing to pay for the gas.

getDefinedKeys(uint256,address,string[]).details: Returns all defined keys (addresses with full access, addresses with fallback access, and child paths) for the node at the given position in the permissions.

getExpiration(uint256,address,string[],a.details: Returns the expiration timestamp for a given operator permission inside the storage.

grant(uint256,address,string[],address,u.details: Tries to grant a particular permission, checking that the sender of the message is actually allowed to do so.

hasAccess(uint256,address,string[],addre.details: Checks if the given address has access permissions to the given token and hierarchy level.  In addition to the actual rules specified in the permissions themselves, the owner address always has access.

onERC721Received(address,address,uint256.details: We accept ERC-721 token transfers only when explicitly specified that we expect one, and we only accept Xaya names at all.

permissionExists(uint256,address,string[.details: Returns true if there is a node with specific permissions at the given hierarchy level (i.e. it exists).
Returns true if a specific permission exists at the given node and for the given operator and fallback type.

registerFor(string,string,address,bytes).details: Registers a name for a given owner.  This registers the name, transfers it, and then sets operator permissions for the delegation contract with the owner's prepared signature.  With this method, we can enable gas-free name registration with this contract's support for meta transactions.  Returns the new token's ID. The WCHI for the name registration is paid for by _msgSender.

resetTree(uint256,address,string[]).details: Revokes all permissions in a given subtree, and replaces them with just a single permission for the message sender.  This can be used to reset an entire tree of permissions if desired, while making sure the message sender retains permission (but they can explicitly revoke their own as well afterwards).  Reverts if the message sender has no access to the requested level.

revoke(uint256,address,string[],address,.details: Revokes a particular approval, checking that the message sender is actually allowed to do so.

sendHierarchicalMove(string,string,strin.details: Sends a move for the given name that contains some JSON data at the given path.  Verifies that the _msgSender is allowed to send a move for that name and path at the current time.  The nonce used is returned (as from XayaAccounts.move). Any WCHI required for the move will be paid for by _msgSender.
Sends a move for the given name as the other sendHierarchicalMove method, but allows control over nonce and WCHI payments.

takeOverName(string,string).details: Takes over a name:  This transfers the name to be owned by the delegation contract (which is irreversible and corresponds to a provable "lock" of the name).  This can only be done by the owner of the name.  The previous owner will be granted top-level permissions, based on which they can then selectively restrict their access if desired.

allowNameReceive.details: Temporarily set to true while we expect to receive name NFTs (e.g. while registering for a user). It allows to receive name ERC721 tokens when set.
